Parliament, Monday, 11 March 2019 – The Ad Hoc Committee to identify suitable candidates for the filling of vacancies at the Commission for Gender Equality (CGE )will tomorrow meet to interview candidates that have been shortlisted. The interviews will take place over a period of two days. The committee shortlisted 24 candidates to be interviewed for appointment to the Commission for Gender Equality. The committee will recommend names for filling of eight vacancies. Details of Tuesday’s meeting: Date: Tuesday, 12 March 2019
	Time: 09:00 - 20:00
	Venue: V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE AD HOC COMMITTEE TO IDENTIFY SUITABLE CANDIDATES FOR THE FILLING OF VACANCIES AT THE COMMISSION FOR GENDER EQUALITY, MS NONHLANHLA NCUBE-NDABA. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Yoliswa Landu
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8203 
	Cell: 081 497 4694
